✨ Over the moon right now introducing to you my new son, that you can Pre-order right now! ✨

I've been hiding this last year because I've been working  with the wonderful @flyingeyebooks on this lovely comic.
The first installment in a new series that tells us the greatest secrets and fears of the monsters we all love! In this one, you will meet Lowell, a young werewolf who will live a really cool adventure trying to find himself.

And what better occasion than this, because @barnesandnoble is talking off 25% off all preorders from January 25 to 27!
So if you want to order your copy of “Monster Support Group: The Werewolf's Tale” with a discount, go to their website and enter the code PREORDER25.✨🌝

Many thanks to Emily, Ivanna, Sussanah and all the Flying team, you are the very best and a dream to work by side.

✨My stardog’s name was Buki.✨ He was older, he had no breed, he was one of those crossbred dogs that were called “for hunting”. He didn’t live in my apartment, he lived in my great-grandparents’ house.

✦ I remember Buki’s happy face jumping up and down when we arrived at his house from the other side of the car window.
✦ I remember Buki holding and walking gingerly with a pebble on his head because I had put it on him, as I had failed to make a flower crown.
✦ I remember Buki growling at strangers when they held me in their arms.
✦ I remember Buki chasing the car running and crying as we were leaving, and me looking back at the window wishing that someday, he would make it home with us.

When Buki died I was about 6 or 7 years old, to keep me from crying I was told for years that Buki was lost and someday he would come back. I don’t have any pictures of him. And when I saw this wonderful #stardogdtiys that @ekmosley.illustration prepared, I couldn’t help butthink of him. Because even though many dogs have passed through my life, Buki will always have a special place in my heart.

I like to imagine him like this, with the stars are caressing him while he waits for me.

Thank you E.K.Mosley for this beautiful challenge, and congratulations on your brilliant book. I can’t wait to read it. ✨🌛💛
.

🤎 Werewolf Mask 🤎
——————————————————————
As Halloween swiftly approaches, we were delighted to revisit one of our favourite books, ‘Monster Support Group - The Werewolf’s Tale.’ 

This brilliant story follows the journey of twelve year old Lowell, who is struggling to fit into his new village, especially when he is secretly a Werewolf! 

This hilariously hairy tale is the first instalment in the series of spooky stories by the phenomenal @laurasuarez 
Laura had a new title releasing this month too! 

To celebrate this awesome book character, we brought Lowell to life, creating a Werewolf mask! An easy craft made simply from cardboard and craft paper. 

Follow our step by step instructions in this reel to craft your own mask this Halloween! 

For more information on how we made our mask and to get a link to this wonderful book, check out @craftedbybears stories / Flying Eye Books Highlight. 

Thank you @flyingeyebooks for introducing us to this incredible book series, the perfect ‘not so scary’ Halloween stories for young readers 🤎

Egyptian Halloween Costume
——————————————————
If you’re looking for an eco /budget friendly Halloween costume this year, this one is for you! 

Inspired by the incredible illustration work of @laurasuarez we brought her main character of ‘Monster Support Group - The Mummy’s Curse’ to life. 

Anatiti is a stubborn pharaoh who never listened to her advisors. After tragedy strikes, Anatiti can’t find her way to the afterlife and after 3000 years seeks the help of her new found monster friends! 

This incredibly well thought out book is packed with stunning illustrations and a cautionary tale for little readers. Laura’s attention to detail is outstanding! 

Our Anatiti was such a simple make, made from cardboard, paint pens, a head band and string! 

We adore homemade Halloween crafts and this brilliant book was the perfect resource for bookish play! 

Head to @craftedbybears stories / Flying Eye Books highlight for a step by step guide to making your own Egyptian costume for the spooky season. 

Happy crafting!
